# flow.js - a javascript flow control micro library

Flow.js is a javascript flow-control micro library. It works in node.js and in browser. It is only 30lines.
It allow to write 

# how to use it

   Flow().seq(function(next){
       console.log("step 1: started, it will last 1sec");
       setTimeout(function(){
           console.log("step 1: 1sec expired. Step1 completed");
           next();
       }, 1000);
   }).seq(function(next){
       console.log("step 2: run after step1 has been completed");
   })

    

